# ── Market Sentiment Engine — API keys (optional) ──────────────────────────
# Copy this file to  config/sentiment.env  and fill in what you have.
# The launchers (start_live.sh / start_live.bat) load it automatically and
# export the vars to the sentiment engine subprocess. Anything left blank stays
# MISSING (neutral) — the engine never fabricates a value, and the trading bot
# is unaffected either way.
#
# This file is a template and is safe to commit. Your real config/sentiment.env
# with live keys should NOT be committed (add it to .gitignore).

# --- FRED (fundamental bias: real yields, Fed funds, dollar trend, CPI) -------
# Free key, ~30 seconds to get one:
#   1. https://fredaccount.stlouisfed.org/apikeys
#   2. Sign up (email) → "Request API Key" → copy the 32-char key
# Without this, the Fundamental component (30 pts) shows MISSING/neutral.
FRED_API_KEY=

# --- DXY level override (caveat: true DXY is an ICE proprietary index) --------
# FRED gives us the dollar DIRECTION (via the broad-dollar index DTWEXBGS), which
# is enough for the proven "never fight the dollar" override. But the spec's
# level-based DXYScore (+10 if DXY<100 & falling, -10 if >105 & rising) needs the
# actual DXY number, which no free API publishes cleanly.
# If you want level-based scoring, paste today's DXY here (e.g. from
# tradingview/investing.com). Leave blank to use direction-only (recommended —
# no stale manual number). Example:
# DXY_LEVEL=98.4
DXY_LEVEL=

# --- Fiscal stress flag (FiscalScore, +5 to Fundamental) ---------------------
# There is no clean free API for "is there a debt-ceiling / shutdown crisis", so
# this is a manual switch. Set it true during a known US fiscal stress episode
# (shutdown, debt-ceiling standoff) — it nudges Fundamental bullish (gold bid).
# Leave blank/false normally. Accepts true/false/1/0/yes/no.
FISCAL_STRESS=

# --- Telegram signal notifications (get pinged when a setup forms) ------------
# The engine pushes actionable AI signals (LONG/SHORT/REDUCE) to Telegram. If
# you leave these blank it falls back to FIREHOSE_* then BOT_TOKEN/CHANNEL_ID
# from trading_bot/.env (so it may already work).
#
# To target a SPECIFIC group: set ONLY SENTIMENT_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID — the token is
# reused from your existing BOT_TOKEN (that bot must be a MEMBER of the group).
# To find the group's chat id:
#   1. Add your bot to the group.
#   2. Post any message in the group, then open
#      https://api.telegram.org/bot<BOT_TOKEN>/getUpdates
#      → find  "chat":{"id":-100xxxxxxxxxx,...}  — that negative number is the id.
# Set SENTIMENT_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN only if you want a DIFFERENT bot.
SENTIMENT_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
SENTIMENT_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=
